  "prompt": "How much money does a Ranji Trophy cricketer earn?",
  "response": "The earnings of a Ranji Trophy cricketer can vary significantly based on several factors, including their experience, performance, and the state association they represent. Here\u2019s a general breakdown:\n\n### Match Fees:\n- **Ranji Trophy Match Fees:** As of the latest information, a player in the Ranji Trophy typically earns around **\u20b940,000** per match day for a first-class game. Since a Ranji Trophy match lasts up to **4 days**, a player can earn up to **\u20b91.6 lakh** per match.\n\n### Additional Earnings:\n- **Winning Bonus:** If the team wins a match, players may receive an additional **\u20b915,000 to \u20b920,000** per player as a winning bonus.\n- **Seasonal Contracts:** Some state associations offer annual contracts to players, which can range from **\u20b910 lakh to \u20b950 lakh** per year, depending on the player's grade (A, B, or C).\n- **Senior Players:** Established players with senior-level experience or those who have played for India or in the IPL may earn significantly more through endorsements and other contracts.\n\n### Practice Matches and Camp Stipends:\n- Players are often paid daily allowances during practice matches or training camps, typically around **\u20b92,000 to \u20b93,000** per day.\n\n### Total Earnings:\nFor an average player who plays all the matches in a season (around 8\u201310 matches), the total earnings can range between **\u20b915 lakh to \u20b925 lakh** per year, excluding endorsements or IPL contracts.\n\n### Note:\nThese figures are approximate and can vary based on the policies of the Board of Control for Cricket in India (BCCI) and individual state cricket associations. Additionally, players who are part of the IPL or have central contracts with the BCCI may earn significantly more.",
